    "body": "### Problem\n\nWrong text is rendered. Changes when moving the cursor.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nI have recorded a video: https://youtu.be/QFh437aVra4\n\nWhile I move my cursor, the text next to it and in other lines changes. I have not changed any of these fundamental settings in a while. It must be a bug introduced in a recent update.\n\n```lua\nvim.opt.cursorcolumn = true\nvim.opt.linebreak = true\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n-\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot applicable\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 26.3.1 (a)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.3.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nHomebrew Release",
